parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses all electrical power
the engine cuts out
the screens go black
the ignition button does not restart the car
the hazard lights do not activate
and the power locks do not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the transmission shifts are not smooth
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Mount and Power Steering Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine mount and power steering can cause the vehicle to vibrate excessively, making it difficult to control, and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The engine mount collapses
the power steering is stiff and hard to turn
and the vehicle vibrates excessively.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the engine to catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine catches fire
the "engine performance decreased" warning light appears on the dashboard
and the "battery not charging" warning light appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the remote keyless drive system can cause safety issues, such as increased risk of theft or carjacking, and can also cause inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: The key fob does not work unless the driver is within 12 inches of the car
the panic button does not work
and the remote start feature does not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the BLIS can cause safety issues, such as increased risk of accidents, and can also cause inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: The passenger-side BLIS fails to indicate vehicles in the blind spot
and the system fails to work intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the accessory plug and fuse can cause safety issues, such as increased risk of electrical fires, and can also cause inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: The 12V accessory plug blows fuses
and the fuses continue to blow even after replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive oil consumption can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents due to engine failure.
symptoms: Oil light comes on
low oil levels
engine running harder than normal
difficulty accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Battery Drain Caused by RDR System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The battery drain can cause the vehicle to shut down, leaving the driver stranded, and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Battery drain
vehicle shut down
difficulty starting the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shut down of the vehicle while driving can cause accidents, especially if it occurs in heavy traffic or at high speeds.
symptoms: Vehicle shut down
loss of power
inability to turn on hazard lights
black screen on electronics
difficulty shifting into neutral.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Blind Spot Information System (BLIS) Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the BLIS can cause accidents, especially when changing lanes or merging with traffic.
symptoms: Intermittent failure of passenger-side BLIS
inconsistent performance of BLIS.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning of the City Safety feature can cause accidents, especially in low-speed situations.
symptoms: Malfunctioning City Safety feature
failure to detect obstacles or vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn can cause accidents, especially when warning other drivers of potential collisions.
symptoms: Horn failure
difficulty activating the horn
excessive resistance when pressing the horn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt locking mechanism can lead to a life-threatening situation, especially for children in car seats, as it may not provide adequate restraint in the event of sudden stops or accidents.
symptoms: The seat belt does not lock after being buckled
the seat belt does not tighten with sudden stops
the seat belt randomly locks or unlocks without warning
the seat belt chokes or constricts the driver or passenger when leaning forward.
